                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17905627" author="chia7712" created="Fri, 13 Dec 2024 22:40:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;    // We use this library to generate OpenAPI docs for the REST API, but we don&apos;t want or need it at compile&lt;br/&gt;
    // or run time. So, we add it to a separate configuration, which we use later on during docs generation&lt;br/&gt;
    swagger libs.swaggerJaxrs2&lt;br/&gt;
    // this is an example to fix this issue&lt;br/&gt;
    swagger group: &apos;javax.ws.rs&apos;, name: &apos;javax.ws.rs-api&apos;, version: &apos;2.1.1&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17905633" author="christopher.l.shannon" created="Fri, 13 Dec 2024 23:20:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t looked into it yet but is there no way to upgrade Swagger to use the new jakarta API instead? That seems like the right approach vs bring back the old jar as those old annotations are not used anymore in the Kafka build.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17905636" author="chia7712" created="Fri, 13 Dec 2024 23:40:13 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;is there no way to upgrade Swagger to use the new jakarta API instead? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I test the latest swagger plugin and it is the same (&lt;a href=&quot;https://plugins.gradle.org/plugin/io.swagger.core.v3.swagger-gradle-plugin&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://plugins.gradle.org/plugin/io.swagger.core.v3.swagger-gradle-plugin&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;bring back the old jar as those old annotations are not used anymore in the Kafka build.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The jar is added only to the Swagger scope (refer to my previous comment), which means it is not included in either the release or test scopes. Please see the attached dependency tree for more details.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17905638" author="christopher.l.shannon" created="Fri, 13 Dec 2024 23:45:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found documentation that says it can support the Jakarta namespace, with some changes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-core/blob/master/modules/swagger-gradle-plugin/README.md#jakarta-namespace-support&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-core/blob/master/modules/swagger-gradle-plugin/README.md#jakarta-namespace-support&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-core/wiki/Swagger-2.X---Getting-started#note-jakarta-namespace-support-since-version-217&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-core/wiki/Swagger-2.X---Getting-started#note-jakarta-namespace-support-since-version-217&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
